cs.IR, cs.DS, cs.DL, cs.CC, cs.CR 

This paper deals with indexing techniques for large repositories of versioned documents, which is a problem relevant to information retrieval (cs.IR). The paper also introduces new compression techniques for inverted indexes, which are data structures commonly used in information retrieval and data structures (cs.DS). The use of run-length, Lempel-Ziv, and grammar compression also suggests a connection to data compression (cs.DL). The paper discusses the trade-off between space and time complexity, which is a common theme in algorithms and complexity (cs.CC). Finally, the paper also mentions the use of compressed self-indexes, which are related to data structures and cryptography (cs.CR).
